<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,589,2030]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,220]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1844,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to the Neotropical species 
<taxonomicName authority="Edwards" authorityName="Edwards" box="[925,1141,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Platyroptilon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zernyi">
<emphasis box="[925,1028,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. zernyi</emphasis>
Edwards
</taxonomicName>
, in having 
<number box="[1276,1305,1844,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="14.0">14</number>
flagellomeres, but it is easily distinguished by the apical two flagellomeres being pale yellow (these flagellomeres are brown in 
<emphasis box="[262,358,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. z e r n y i</emphasis>
) and the distinct difference between the shape of their gonostylus. Having compared 
<emphasis box="[1358,1425,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. w u i</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,218,1964,1990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">n. sp.</emphasis>
with the Oriental species 
<taxonomicName authority="Matile" authorityName="Matile" box="[525,779,1964,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Platyroptilon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirkspriggsi">
<emphasis box="[525,695,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. kirkspriggsi</emphasis>
Matile
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[837,950,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. s c u r ro r</emphasis>
Matile, we have found that the new species differs in having 
<number box="[419,448,2004,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="14.0">14</number>
flagellomeres (only 
<number box="[702,731,2004,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="12.0">12</number>
flagellomeres in the two mentioned species), radiomedial fusion 
<number box="[233,269,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" value="1.3">1.3</number>
x length of petiole of M (
<number box="[574,612,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" value="0.5">0.5</number>
x in 
<taxonomicName box="[668,838,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Platyroptilon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirkspriggsi">
<emphasis box="[668,838,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">P. kirkspriggsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 1.0x in 
<emphasis box="[991,1104,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">P. s c u r ro r</emphasis>
) and M 
<number box="[1204,1212,168,182]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
not reaching wing margin (reaching it in the other two species). The shape of the gonostylus is also characteristic of 
<emphasis box="[1286,1352,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">P. w u i</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1363,1429,194,220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">n. sp.</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
